ul.li:
Some of the formatting process needs to be run more than once.
This is why there is the temporary directory mentioned above. It stores the files needs to record the information needed between passes. This means that you may well need to perform the process that produces PDF two or three times before the result is just right. This is especially the case for things like
the PDF bookmarks to appear correctly;
index page numbers to appear correctly;
contents page numbers to appear correctly; and
long tables to format correctly.
